# Build context is the MONOREPO ROOT (see Dockerfile), so the root
# .dockerignore governs what Docker sends. This file mirrors those excludes for
# BuildKit's per-Dockerfile ignore convention (apps/web/Dockerfile ->
# apps/web/.dockerignore) and for a standalone `docker build apps/web` — its
# patterns are written relative to the build context root.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
.git
**/*.log
